set-bg: img/3rd_October_2017.jpg
new-page: true

> * I like Catalan people because \[...\] they do stuff. *

 - Mariano Rajoy, President of the Government of Spain, 2015

This is a game of alternate history. While historical accuracy is a major concern, keep in mind that this is a *game*, and that any divergence from actual events will necessarily have to involve some element of make-believe. Nevertheless, please let the author know if there are any glaring mistakes.

For more information on the politics, government, and recent history of Catalonia, please see the Library page on the top left. If this is your first time playing the game, it is strongly recommended that you read at least some of this information.

**If you are playing this mod via the Mod Loader in base game, you may be using a broken build. For the intended experience, please play using <a class="link" href="https://broken-arrows.github.io/route_to_itaca/" style="color: #0077FF; text-de">this</a> link.**

- @easy_mode : Begin - <span style="color: #5B9A8D;font-weight: bold;">Easy</span>
- @normal_mode : Begin - <span style="color: #C4B156;font-weight: bold;">Normal</span>
- @hard_mode : Begin - <span style="color: #943006ff;font-weight: bold;">Hard</span>

@easy_mode
title: Begin - Easy
on-arrival: difficulty = -1; erc_resources = 4; ciu_resources = 4; cup_resources = 5; m_k_relation = 50; m_sr_relation = 62; sr_k_relation = 50; m_split_threshold = 65; sr_split_threshold = 65; m_support_change = 10; sr_support_change = 10; m_discipline_change = 8; sr_discipline_change = 8; max_advisors = 5; ipr_change = 8;
