@ciu
title: Convergence and Union (CiU)
face-image: img/parties/logo_ciu.png

**Convergence and Union - CiU**

The center-right nationalist federation of the liberal Democratic Convergence of Catalonia (CDC) and the christian Democratic Union of Catalonia (UDC) has positioned itself as the moderately autonomist with pro-business policies force. It governed Catalonia almost undisputed in the post-Franco autonomy era, and has come back again in 2010 under Artur Mas, who has long championed fiscal autonomy. Nonetheless, the statute reform's partial rollback fueled internal debates on independence. In 2012, it faces strong austerity backlash and a voter shift to harder-line pro-independence options.

- @ciu_2: Yes, I am a convergent!
- @party_selection: No, select a different party.


@ciu_2
choose-if: 1==0
unavailable-subtitle: Work in progress...
on-arrival: player_party = "ciu"; position_disp = "<span style='color: var(--ciu);'>Generalitat (minority government)</span>";
go-to: intros

@cup
title: Popular Unity Candidacy (CUP)
face-image: img/parties/logo_cup.svg

**Popular Unity Candidacy - CUP**

The far-left, anti-capitalist, eco-socialist platform demands direct democracy, independence, and municipalism. Emerging from 1980s local assemblies, until recently it had a strong grassroots focus and avoided institutions. In 2012, it is getting ready for its first elections, posing as the "left alternative" and pledging one-term mandates and anti-austerity. How much it is able to scale nationally may very well depend on its ability to remain internally coherent and united.

- @cup_2: Yes, it's the time of the peoples!
- @party_selection: No, select a different party.


